Chairman of Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC), Hon. Abdullahi Adamu Candido, has felicitated with the Christian residents in AMAC, urging them to imbibe the teachings of Jesus Christ in their daily conducts. Candido also implored Christians to imbibe the tenets of tolerance and unity, irrespective of ethnic and religious differences, so as to achieve peaceful coexistence among the various ethnic groups in the area council. In his Easter message delivered through his special assistant on media and public relations, Dayo Lawal, the AMAC chairman advised residents to imbibe the tenets of love, tolerance, forgiveness and brotherhood which the period of Easter festivities exemplify. He maintained that it is only by embracing peace, unity and fairness that meaningful progress and development could be achieved, just as he called on residents to pray for the council and its leadership, for continued transformation through the provision of social amenities and good governance.